Populate makes the most sense in Abzan, I think. Black leans a little bit more into big tokens, and you still have root green/white.

Madness should be a fun rakdos deck, I would be surprised if they made it three color.

Flashback is an interesting one, and is pretty fairly spread out among all the colors, with white having the least and red having the most. As for it making sense in a color scheme, I dunno... I think I would more approach this as "what colors would be **fun** with flashback", rather than "what colors own flashback". With that in mind, I wouldn't be amazed to see this as either Boros or Jeskai, although the cynic in me assumes it will just be Sultai with the ability to bring things back from exile.

Morph isn't Temur, and would make a ton of sense as a 5 color deck. Given that we've had so many 5 color commanders lately, however, I think it's more likely we'll see this as Simic or Bant.
To be fair, we've been seeing some token stuff in blue, haven't we? Murmuring Mystic comes to mind, I think a couple of other things...?
Monastery Mentor reprint confirmed??
I don’t disagree with any of that. I think Blue’s ability to make token copies makes a more compelling/ interesting space than Black’s token generation, but that’s me.

Populate seems far more likely to be Naya than Abzan. Red's been upping the token game recently, and Abzan already has a precon token commander, and Bant got a deck last year.
I'm with you on Madness, I can't see them stretching it to Grixis when it works so well as Rakdos
